This paper discusses the integration of XML and Semantic Web technologies, specifically through the use of SPARQL and XQuery. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), software engineering (cs.SE), and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper's focus on schema mapping, schema transformation, and query translation further supports these potential sub-categories.
